com.gnahraf.io.buffer

Class SortedBlock

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gnahraf.io.buffer.Block
      • com.gnahraf.io.buffer.SortedBlock
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sorted
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SortedViewBlock

    public class SortedBlock
extends Block
implements Sorted
    Marker for a sorted Block. There's no real guarantee that a given instance's underlying buffer's contents is sorted; that would be too expensive to enforce, and consequently sorted-ness is honorary. Suffice to say, results are defined when you break the rules.
    Author:
    Babak

      public int binarySearch(ByteBuffer key, int fromIndex, int toIndex) {
        return Arrays.binarySearch(cells, fromIndex, toIndex, key, order);
      }
